<subSubSection id="C2D031637D3DDB92CB8857F86B5CB06A" pageId="0" pageNumber="203" type="notes">
<paragraph id="77AA4F04DA71DE59F832B1C16BE9AD26" pageId="0" pageNumber="203">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F8DA1055F142FD0C92B97D19C7CDBAB6" pageId="0" pageNumber="203">
This species was originally described by 
<bibRefCitation id="8A7EAA6431C9F4ED78EC83B406841490" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1017/S0960428619000052" author="Hughes, M" journalOrPublisher="Edinburgh Journal of Botany" pageId="0" pageNumber="203" pagination="1 - 11" refId="B8" refString="Hughes, M, Aung, M, Armstrong, K, 2019. An updated checklist and a new species of Begonia (B. rheophytica) from Myanmar. Edinburgh Journal of Botany 76 (2): 1 - 11, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1017/S0960428619000052" title="An updated checklist and a new species of Begonia (B. rheophytica) from Myanmar." url="https://doi.org/10.1017/S0960428619000052" volume="76" year="2019">Hughes et al. (2019)</bibRefCitation>
from the male flowering plant only. Here, we provide a supplementary description of 
<taxonomicName id="51135251159227A51D170F4CC2E7A4F5" genus="B." lsidName="B. rheophytica" pageId="0" pageNumber="203" rank="species" species="rheophytica">
<emphasis id="635F288A7B6A06DFA9D8AE0F6072EC49" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="203">B. rheophytica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with a detailed monograph of female flowers from Putao, Kachin State, Northern Myanmar.
</paragraph>
